The police in Limpopo have asked members of the public who have information relating to the disappearance of a 20-year-old woman in October to please come forward Police spokesperson Monaste Mamabolo said Pholosho Salvation Sebola, from Makgofe village outside Seshego, was wearing maroon tight shorts and a jersey when she went missing. “She is of average body build, light in complexion, with long hair,” Mamabolo said. Anyone with information on Sebola’s whereabouts can contact Warrant Officer Mangakeng on 082 878 8525 or contact their nearest police station. Alternatively, anyone can call Crime Stop on 08600 10 111 or SMS Crime line on 32211. -TNA Reporter